<item>
            <title>[LU-8914] write call hung in wait_on_page_bit</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8914</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;write system call hangs with identical stack to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4540&quot; title=&quot;Test failure sanity-quota test_8: dbench hung in vvp_page_assume&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4540&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4540&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Comments in that ticket ascribe the error to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3321&quot; title=&quot;2.x single thread/process throughput degraded from 1.8&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3321&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3321&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; commits, however our patch stack does not have most of the &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3321&quot; title=&quot;2.x single thread/process throughput degraded from 1.8&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3321&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3321&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; commits.  The only one I found is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4786&quot; title=&quot;Apparent denial of service from client to mdt&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4786&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4786&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; osc: to not pick busy pages for ELC&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;so it&apos;s unclear to me whether the problem we are seeing is due to the same root cause.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>lustre-2.5.5-10chaos.4&lt;br/&gt;
rhel 7.3</environment>
